WEBVTT

00:13.535 --> 00:15.450
[Bazza]
You should do me one favor.

00:15.580 --> 00:19.845
Don't give up. You'll get
to America in the end.

00:19.976 --> 00:20.716
[Alfred] Let's get down
to business, shall we?

00:20.846 --> 00:23.023
I'm getting to America.

00:23.153 --> 00:25.590
If you've got something that
could make that happen, I'm in.

00:25.721 --> 00:27.462
I might just have something.

00:27.592 --> 00:29.855
We've made
no fucking progress at all!

00:29.986 --> 00:32.641
If London falls, the northern
cities will surrender.

00:32.771 --> 00:35.557
Full-scale artillery
bombardment will do the trick.

00:35.687 --> 00:38.516
League council are electing
a new prime minister.

00:38.647 --> 00:40.301
As you may have heard,
the last one killed himself.

00:40.431 --> 00:43.304
This good woman is
the rightful queen of England,

00:43.434 --> 00:46.655
and we are the rightful
government of England.

00:46.785 --> 00:48.526
I have no gift for politics,

00:48.657 --> 00:50.876
but this new chap Aziz
might listen to reason.

00:51.007 --> 00:52.704
It had occurred to me.

00:52.835 --> 00:54.576
[Peggy]
Where the hell have you been?

00:54.706 --> 00:55.751
[Sykes] Round and about.

00:55.881 --> 00:57.448
This is me friend Katie.

00:57.579 --> 00:58.841
I've told her nowt
about me past,

00:58.971 --> 01:00.712
and you'll do likewise, eh?

01:00.843 --> 01:03.498
-Are you trying to seduce me?
-I guess I am.

01:03.628 --> 01:06.283
I've never been seduced by
a crypto-fascist bastard before.

01:06.414 --> 01:07.806
[Melanie] I'm going home.

01:07.937 --> 01:08.851
No. You leave
when I say you can leave.

01:08.981 --> 01:10.200
Fuck you.

01:12.115 --> 01:14.509
I'm Gully Troy,
and you don't cross me.

01:14.639 --> 01:16.293
I'm Alfred Pennyworth,
and I just did.

01:16.424 --> 01:19.079
Thank you for helping me.

01:21.646 --> 01:24.388
Ancillary technical staff.
Dr. Lucius Fox.

01:24.519 --> 01:25.694
[Salt] Ladies and gentlemen,
you're about to see

01:25.824 --> 01:28.523
a demonstration of Stormcloud.

01:28.653 --> 01:30.264
This is the future
of chemical warfare.

01:32.309 --> 01:36.705
[Harwood] This is victory,
ladies and gentlemen. Victory.

01:47.411 --> 01:48.456
[door closes]

01:48.586 --> 01:50.284
[crowd screaming in distance]

01:50.414 --> 01:53.243
[panting]

01:55.419 --> 01:56.594
Get out of my way!

01:59.510 --> 02:00.642
Fuck.

02:00.772 --> 02:02.252
Get out of my way!

02:04.428 --> 02:06.474
Die, you evil bastard!

02:06.604 --> 02:08.737
[yelling]

02:10.391 --> 02:11.696
No! Stop!

02:11.827 --> 02:14.525
[gunshot]

02:14.656 --> 02:17.528
You once told me you could
get me on a plane to America.

02:17.659 --> 02:21.663
Well, times have changed.
Everyone and his dog wants out.

02:21.793 --> 02:23.012
Well, the embassy
still operates

02:23.143 --> 02:24.753
a regular flight out
once a week,

02:24.883 --> 02:28.148
but there are hundreds
on the waiting list.

02:28.278 --> 02:31.020
I need three seats
on next week's flight to Gotham.

02:31.151 --> 02:34.763
Seats are like gold dust.
Air crews are on the take.

02:34.893 --> 02:36.330
Customs are on the take.
Immigration--

02:36.460 --> 02:37.940
I didn't think
we'd fly for free.

02:38.070 --> 02:39.289
How much?

02:41.900 --> 02:43.424
Well, five grand a head?

02:43.554 --> 02:45.817
Fuck.

02:45.948 --> 02:47.906
-I thought half that, tops.
-Mm.

02:48.037 --> 02:49.908
That's a conservative estimate.

02:50.039 --> 02:53.608
-You can't make that?
-Not at this exact moment, no.

02:55.523 --> 02:57.873
Well, maybe I could help.

02:58.003 --> 02:59.570
How?

02:59.701 --> 03:01.181
I could loan you the money
you need.

03:01.311 --> 03:04.401
Oh. That's very kind of you.
No, thanks.

03:04.532 --> 03:06.621
-It's no bother at all.
-No.

03:06.751 --> 03:08.144
Why not?

03:08.275 --> 03:10.320
I'd rather not be in debt
to the CIA.

03:10.451 --> 03:11.365
I know where that leads.

03:13.062 --> 03:15.847
-No strings. Between friends.
-[chuckles]

03:17.458 --> 03:19.329
We are friends, aren't we?

03:19.460 --> 03:21.723
You can call it that.

03:21.853 --> 03:23.507
Thanks all the same.

03:23.638 --> 03:26.597
I'll get your money for you.
No problem.

03:31.602 --> 03:35.867
[Thomas]
File 457NFH. Contact log 35.

03:35.998 --> 03:38.087
Alfred Pennyworth.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.611
Subject made contact seeking
assistance regarding travel to

03:40.742 --> 03:44.049
and residence in America.

03:44.180 --> 03:47.531
Subject is a recruitment target
of long standing.

03:49.751 --> 03:51.709
Good morning, sleepyhead.

03:51.840 --> 03:53.494
Morning.

03:57.149 --> 03:58.977
[chuckles]

04:06.202 --> 04:07.595
-Oh, my God.
-I know.

04:07.725 --> 04:09.292
-Oh.
-What did I do wrong?

04:10.554 --> 04:12.774
Of course you don't know
how to make coffee.

04:12.904 --> 04:15.037
-You have people for that.
-I do.

04:15.167 --> 04:17.605
And I'll bring them along
next time.

04:17.735 --> 04:20.129
I really have to get going.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.783
What are you doing today?

04:23.611 --> 04:26.440
Just, um, routine sentry duty.

04:27.876 --> 04:29.007
You've been pretty busy

04:29.138 --> 04:31.749
-with the League lately.
-I guess.

04:31.880 --> 04:34.404
You're not putting yourself
in too much danger, I hope.

04:34.535 --> 04:35.405
Are you?

04:38.321 --> 04:40.932
Is it my imagination or are you
pumping me for information?

04:41.063 --> 04:43.500
No. No, certainly not.

04:43.631 --> 04:45.894
I worry about you, that's all.

04:46.024 --> 04:48.113
-You don't worry about me?
-No.

04:48.244 --> 04:51.856
I assume you can take care
of yourself, like I can.

04:51.987 --> 04:53.249
Well, I figure when you're
in a relationship,

04:53.380 --> 04:55.730
people, they-they
look out for each other.

04:55.860 --> 04:57.079
This is what,
the third time we've had sex?

04:57.209 --> 04:59.995
-Fourth.
-Okay, fourth.

05:00.125 --> 05:03.477
That's not a relationship.
That's sex four times.

05:03.607 --> 05:06.131
It's a sex thing.

05:06.262 --> 05:08.133
And you're actually
pretty good for a rich guy.

05:08.264 --> 05:11.093
Oh, gee, thanks.

05:11.223 --> 05:13.051
Well, if this,
if this "sex thing" is

05:13.182 --> 05:14.618
ever gonna
turn into a relationship,

05:14.749 --> 05:15.880
then we'll-we'll need
to be spending

05:16.011 --> 05:17.012
a certain amount
of time together.

05:17.142 --> 05:20.581
Okay. Well, I really have to go.

05:20.711 --> 05:23.018
Uh, like, for instance,
right now.

05:23.148 --> 05:25.629
Can't League business
wait a couple of hours?

05:25.760 --> 05:27.936
No. It's important.

05:28.066 --> 05:30.068
Sentry duty? Really?

05:30.199 --> 05:31.592
You're trying to make me mad.

05:31.722 --> 05:33.028
You are pumping me
for information.

05:33.158 --> 05:35.900
C-I-fucking-A to the bone.

05:36.031 --> 05:37.946
I give up.

05:38.076 --> 05:39.469
Well, you can't just go
through life pretending

05:39.600 --> 05:41.645
you like being alone.

05:41.776 --> 05:43.343
Now, I know it's very,
very fashionable and modern.

05:43.473 --> 05:45.214
I-I'm not pretending.
I'm not pretending.

05:45.345 --> 05:46.650
But, Jesus, would an--
would an actual relationship

05:46.781 --> 05:48.652
be that bad?

05:48.783 --> 05:50.741
I mean, let's be honest,
most women would,

05:50.872 --> 05:52.743
-they would...
-[laughs softly]

05:52.874 --> 05:54.832
[stammers]

05:54.963 --> 05:56.617
Oh, no, please continue.

05:56.747 --> 05:58.314
Go on.

05:58.445 --> 06:01.230
Tell me what, um,
most women would do.

06:01.361 --> 06:04.755
Most women wouldn't try so hard
to get themselves killed.

06:04.886 --> 06:06.844
It's like you want to get hurt.

06:06.975 --> 06:10.631
It's like somewhere deep inside,
you hate yourself.

06:13.285 --> 06:15.287
It's true.

06:15.418 --> 06:17.855
I don't love myself quite
as much as you love yourself,

06:17.986 --> 06:20.292
but, um, that's kind
of healthy, I think.

06:20.423 --> 06:23.905
Learn to hate yourself a little
bit more, be good for your soul.

06:24.035 --> 06:26.690
See how you work. When you make
someone else feel bad

06:26.821 --> 06:28.170
about themselves,
you feel good about yourself.

06:28.300 --> 06:29.258
You're a self-esteem vampire.

06:29.389 --> 06:31.173
Maybe you should leave now.

06:31.303 --> 06:32.827
Okay, I...

06:32.957 --> 06:34.219
I take that back.
That was unfair.

06:34.350 --> 06:36.265
Wh-- Unfair
because it's not true

06:36.396 --> 06:37.527
or unfair because it's true?

06:37.658 --> 06:39.660
I misspoke.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.794
You're not Dracula. But you...

06:46.057 --> 06:48.233
...you do have some tendencies.

06:48.364 --> 06:49.931
You know what? Fuck you.

06:50.061 --> 06:51.933
I rest my case.

06:57.329 --> 06:58.940
Ugh.

06:59.070 --> 07:00.028
Clean your goddamn apartment.

07:00.158 --> 07:01.725
-[scoffs]
-Slob.

07:04.293 --> 07:05.903
-[door closes]
-[scoffs]

07:09.080 --> 07:13.476
I've thought about you often
since we met so strangely.

07:13.607 --> 07:17.045
-How are you faring?
-Well enough, ma'am. And you?

07:17.175 --> 07:19.787
Oh, one god-awful ghastly thing
after another.

07:19.917 --> 07:21.136
I'm sorry to hear that.

07:21.266 --> 07:23.965
Keep out of politics, my dear.

07:24.095 --> 07:26.097
Where on earth
are you taking me?

07:30.841 --> 07:32.713
[clears throat, laughs softly]

07:50.382 --> 07:51.993
Welcome.

07:52.123 --> 07:53.777
A pleasure to meet you,
Dr. Gaunt.

07:53.908 --> 07:55.475
Prime Minister.

07:55.605 --> 07:57.259
Martha, thank you so much
for arranging this.

07:57.389 --> 07:59.087
-You are a treasure.
-Isn't she?

07:59.217 --> 08:01.437
The minute I met her,
I knew she was special.

08:01.568 --> 08:03.134
Uh, well,
I'll leave you guys to it.

08:03.265 --> 08:04.832
And we have guards
surrounding the place,

08:04.962 --> 08:07.008
so you won't be disturbed.

08:08.400 --> 08:09.619
Please.

08:10.881 --> 08:12.927
Odd venue.

08:13.057 --> 08:15.712
It was one
of my favorite restaurants.

08:15.843 --> 08:18.759
Exquisite cassoulet. Mmm.

08:18.889 --> 08:20.412
Alas.

08:20.543 --> 08:23.111
I was surprised to hear
from you.

08:25.113 --> 08:27.898
I wanted to open channels
of communication--

08:28.029 --> 08:30.161
-discreet channels.
-Why now?

08:30.292 --> 08:32.207
I've wanted to speak
to the League for some time,

08:32.337 --> 08:35.906
but Archbishop Potter
was an amiable zealot.

08:36.037 --> 08:38.648
I hear that you're
a reasonable man.

08:38.779 --> 08:40.520
I've heard the same of you.

08:40.650 --> 08:42.522
Well, let's reason
with each other, shall we?

08:42.652 --> 08:44.175
Well, I'd love to do that,
but I'm afraid

08:44.306 --> 08:47.744
Lord Harwood and I are
old acquaintances.

08:47.875 --> 08:49.137
A good man in many respects

08:49.267 --> 08:51.356
but not near
as reasonable as we are.

08:51.487 --> 08:53.184
Great leaders are often
more passionate

08:53.315 --> 08:54.708
than they are reasonable,
don't you find?

08:54.838 --> 08:56.536
[both chuckle]

08:56.666 --> 08:58.450
I'm happy to talk
in either case, but do you speak

08:58.581 --> 09:00.148
for Harwood and the Union
or for yourself?

09:00.278 --> 09:02.454
I speak for the good
of the English people.

09:02.585 --> 09:05.806
Ah. How can I refuse
such virtue?

09:05.936 --> 09:09.026
If you were to agree,
a cease-fire,

09:09.157 --> 09:11.942
a negotiated surrender
on honorable terms,

09:12.073 --> 09:13.335
what would those terms be?

09:13.465 --> 09:15.598
Surrender.

09:15.729 --> 09:17.426
-I hadn't considered the notion.
-Of course you have.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.907
Have the Army, the Navy,
the Air Force solidly behind us.

09:20.037 --> 09:21.561
London is surrounded.

09:21.691 --> 09:22.997
You have, what,
five percent of the country?

09:23.127 --> 09:24.564
Geographically.

09:24.694 --> 09:28.480
Psychologically,
I'd say we were still ahead.

09:28.611 --> 09:32.876
You've conquered cities,
not souls.

09:33.007 --> 09:34.486
I don't think you understand
the seriousness

09:34.617 --> 09:37.315
of the situation,
Prime Minister.

09:37.446 --> 09:39.491
We haven't even used
our most effective weapons yet.

09:39.622 --> 09:41.842
We've been showing
great restraint.

09:41.972 --> 09:44.192
Oh, yes, your secret weapon.

09:45.323 --> 09:47.238
Stormcloud, is it?

09:47.369 --> 09:49.545
-What is that, exactly?
-You tell me.

09:49.676 --> 09:51.155
No, no, no.
We know all about it.

09:51.286 --> 09:52.504
I was just curious
to know if you know.

09:52.635 --> 09:55.246
Perhaps Harwood
compartmentalizes

09:55.377 --> 09:56.508
such sensitive matters.

09:56.639 --> 09:59.076
You know nothing
about Stormcloud.

09:59.207 --> 10:01.731
If you did,
you'd be happy to surrender.

10:03.080 --> 10:05.169
-[panting]
-So tell me.

10:05.300 --> 10:08.172
God help you if Stormcloud
is ever deployed.

10:08.303 --> 10:10.392
God help all of us.

10:10.522 --> 10:13.221
Dear me.
Old Testament stuff, eh?

10:13.351 --> 10:16.354
Yes.

10:16.485 --> 10:19.836
I wish I could tell you more.

10:19.967 --> 10:21.577
Your message in summary--

10:21.708 --> 10:24.101
we should surrender
to vague terroristic threats.

10:24.232 --> 10:26.843
You should come to terms
with reality, Prime Minister.

10:26.974 --> 10:29.629
The League holds London.

10:29.759 --> 10:31.369
You daren't destroy
the city to pry us loose.

10:31.500 --> 10:34.285
The world's opinion
would not forgive you.

10:34.416 --> 10:36.853
While we hold London,
I am the prime minister

10:36.984 --> 10:38.942
of Her Rightful Majesty's
government.

10:39.073 --> 10:41.945
We are England.

10:42.076 --> 10:44.469
You are just
political criminals.

10:44.600 --> 10:46.036
That's reality.

10:49.997 --> 10:53.087
Fuck's sake. That much?

10:53.217 --> 10:54.784
Yeah.

10:54.915 --> 10:56.438
Fuck's sake.

10:56.568 --> 10:58.658
Hold on.

10:58.788 --> 11:00.660
That means we don't have
enough money, Alfie.

11:00.790 --> 11:03.140
Yeah, mate.
That's what I've been saying.

11:03.271 --> 11:06.448
Oh, fuck.

11:06.578 --> 11:09.451
Alfie, guess what.
You'll never guess.

11:09.581 --> 11:11.888
It's good news. Guess.

11:12.019 --> 11:14.151
Your dad's joined the circus?

11:14.282 --> 11:16.153
Gertcha. Pukka whistle, this.
Look at that lining.

11:16.284 --> 11:17.328
Arm and a leg, mate.

11:17.459 --> 11:19.200
-Guess.
-Tell.

11:19.330 --> 11:21.028
-She's only making a record.
-Dad.

11:21.158 --> 11:22.551
I wanted to tell him.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.292
-I'm making a record.
-Yes!

11:24.422 --> 11:27.208
Yeah. Brilliant.
Well done. Oh...

11:27.338 --> 11:29.558
Well, it's just a demo for
the record company, but, still,

11:29.689 --> 11:31.342
-it's a record.
-Aye.

11:31.473 --> 11:34.258
It's a "solid smash,"
as we call it.

11:34.389 --> 11:36.957
Will you come
to the recording session?

11:37.087 --> 11:38.349
Please?

11:38.480 --> 11:40.351
Uh, yeah, sure. I'll try.

11:40.482 --> 11:43.528
-You always say that.
-And I always try.

11:43.659 --> 11:47.097
Please come.
I sing better when I feel safe.

11:49.012 --> 11:50.361
Yeah, I'll be there.

11:51.580 --> 11:53.103
Thank you.

11:53.234 --> 11:55.889
-Bye, Daveboy.
-Keep well, then.

11:56.019 --> 11:57.717
Be cool, boys.

12:00.502 --> 12:02.896
I do not believe you.

12:03.026 --> 12:05.072
-What?
-For shame.

12:06.203 --> 12:07.988
Yeah, all right, all right.
Leave it out.

12:08.118 --> 12:10.033
-I'm not in the mood.
-Oh, poor you.

12:10.164 --> 12:12.209
You're not in the mood?
That time of the month,

12:12.340 --> 12:13.602
-is it?
-Leave it alone.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.299
Away forever in a week,

12:15.430 --> 12:17.040
and you've still
not told the poor lassie?

12:17.171 --> 12:19.129
Well, we're not going anywhere,
are we?

12:19.260 --> 12:22.219
We ain't got the money.
That's the problem, not Sandra.

12:22.350 --> 12:25.222
Soon as we know we're going,
I'll tell her, all right?

12:25.353 --> 12:26.963
I'll tell her. Fuck's sake.

12:27.094 --> 12:29.357
All right, all right.
I'll leave it alone.

12:29.487 --> 12:32.142
First we need money.

12:32.273 --> 12:34.318
Well, that's easy enough.

12:34.449 --> 12:37.017
We need to swallow our pride
and do one last job with Gully.

12:37.147 --> 12:40.324
-You think so?
-What else can we do?

12:40.455 --> 12:42.022
I don't know,
but Gully's dangerous.

12:42.152 --> 12:44.111
[chuckles]
Mad as a hatter,

12:44.241 --> 12:45.547
but we knew that
before we took the last job.

12:45.677 --> 12:48.158
So what's the difference now?

12:48.289 --> 12:51.422
True. No difference, really.

12:54.425 --> 12:57.341
So, you think we should do it?
One more job with Gully?

12:57.472 --> 13:00.214
-What do you think?
-I'm asking you.

13:00.344 --> 13:01.693
I don't know.
You're the decision maker.

13:01.824 --> 13:03.783
Well, why's it always me
that has to decide?

13:03.913 --> 13:06.002
Why the fuck can't you do
the thinking for once?

13:06.133 --> 13:07.743
Really?
After all these years, now?

13:07.874 --> 13:10.180
Now you want me
to do the thinking?

13:10.311 --> 13:12.922
-You're going soft, man.
-Eh...

13:14.750 --> 13:16.839
What's got into you?

13:39.079 --> 13:40.297
Thoughts?

13:40.428 --> 13:42.996
[Alfred] Easy enough entry.

13:43.126 --> 13:44.432
No good way out.

13:44.562 --> 13:47.522
There's always a good way out.

13:47.652 --> 13:49.480
You're the expert.

13:50.742 --> 13:53.136
I need to be sure of you, Alfie.

13:54.355 --> 13:59.534
You've been a little, uh,
flighty recently.

13:59.664 --> 14:02.842
Personal problems, hmm?

14:04.539 --> 14:07.281
Don't worry about me. I'm in.

14:09.370 --> 14:10.980
Good enough.

14:13.243 --> 14:15.680
If you do have problems,
I hope you know

14:15.811 --> 14:19.510
that you can always come
to me for advice...

14:21.338 --> 14:23.906
...encouragement.

14:25.386 --> 14:27.170
Thanks.

14:30.347 --> 14:32.306
Uh, should we say, uh,

14:32.436 --> 14:37.920
1100 hours on Friday at...
my house?

14:42.577 --> 14:45.014
[Alfred] Your house?

14:45.145 --> 14:46.581
Yes.

14:50.019 --> 14:52.021
Well, wouldn't somewhere neutral
be better?

14:54.067 --> 14:55.155
No.

14:58.680 --> 15:00.900
Your place it is, then.

15:08.429 --> 15:10.387
♪

15:39.851 --> 15:41.984
♪

15:58.435 --> 16:00.263
[birds cawing]

16:03.658 --> 16:05.529
[door closes in distance]

16:09.446 --> 16:10.708
[door clangs open]

16:15.887 --> 16:17.977
[door slams]

16:31.468 --> 16:33.296
[laughter in distance]

16:33.427 --> 16:35.255
[indistinct chatter]

17:01.324 --> 17:02.847
[static crackling]

17:02.978 --> 17:04.675
[high-pitched ringing]

17:12.031 --> 17:13.423
[footsteps approaching]

17:24.521 --> 17:25.522
[door closes in distance]

17:32.007 --> 17:34.053
[laughs softly]

17:43.671 --> 17:45.629
[sighs]

17:47.501 --> 17:49.329
[device whirring]

18:14.005 --> 18:16.095
♪

18:24.886 --> 18:27.628
[grunts] Unhand me!

18:44.035 --> 18:45.298
What is it?

18:45.428 --> 18:47.343
It's Mrs. Gaunt, sir.

18:47.474 --> 18:49.171
What happened? Is she all right?

18:49.302 --> 18:51.521
The security branch informs us
that Mrs. Gaunt held

18:51.652 --> 18:55.264
a face-to-face meeting with
Prime Minister Aziz yesterday.

18:58.746 --> 19:00.487
Yeah. I knew all about that.

19:00.617 --> 19:01.966
Sir?

19:02.097 --> 19:04.534
I instructed her to contact him.

19:04.665 --> 19:06.971
She's keeping me well-informed.

19:07.102 --> 19:10.105
Good. That's a relief.

19:10.236 --> 19:12.934
I trust the meeting
was constructive.

19:13.064 --> 19:15.154
Well, that's as maybe,
but it's none of your affair.

19:15.284 --> 19:17.547
These are matters of state
beyond your ken.

19:17.678 --> 19:19.549
-Yes, sir, I just...
-Beyond your ken,

19:19.680 --> 19:21.160
do you hear?

19:43.443 --> 19:44.487
Clerk.

19:47.795 --> 19:50.754
I want to call a private
North London number.

19:53.583 --> 19:55.324
-[door closes]
-[entry bell jingles]

19:58.762 --> 20:00.416
Good evening, sir.

20:00.547 --> 20:02.636
Half price on all leather items.

20:09.730 --> 20:11.906
Uh, would that include
truncheons?

20:12.036 --> 20:14.778
It would. Uh, we've
a larger range in stockroom

20:14.909 --> 20:16.606
if you don't see
one there that you like.

20:22.351 --> 20:25.528
Do you have this
with more of a glossy finish?

20:25.659 --> 20:27.965
-More of a formal look.
-[phone ringing]

20:28.096 --> 20:31.621
Yeah, I think so. Let's see.

20:32.927 --> 20:34.929
Get the phone, would you, Bet?

20:35.059 --> 20:37.236
-[Sykes] I'm busy!
-I'm with a customer! [chuckles]

20:43.938 --> 20:45.983
What are you looking at, chubs?

20:47.246 --> 20:49.030
Uh, nothing. I'm-I'm not...

20:49.160 --> 20:50.379
I mean...

20:52.468 --> 20:53.774
I know you.

20:53.904 --> 20:55.428
[phone continues ringing]

20:58.735 --> 21:00.694
Where do I know you from?

21:05.655 --> 21:08.832
You're that beefeater
from the Tower.

21:08.963 --> 21:10.921
-Oh, fuckery.
-I don't know who you are.

21:11.052 --> 21:12.836
I've, I've never seen you
before.

21:12.967 --> 21:14.838
[phone ringing]

21:23.760 --> 21:25.675
[phone line ringing]

21:27.155 --> 21:28.983
Sorry, sir, no one's answering.

21:34.771 --> 21:36.947
[exhales]

21:41.517 --> 21:42.431
Now, then...

21:43.911 --> 21:45.304
...what's your name?

21:46.522 --> 21:48.698
Tell us your name!

21:48.829 --> 21:51.658
-What the hell?
-No bother.

21:51.788 --> 21:54.313
He's an old friend.
Just can't remember his name.

21:58.055 --> 22:00.275
-G-George.
-George.

22:00.406 --> 22:02.799
-Of course.
-Please let me go. I--

22:02.930 --> 22:04.801
I won't tell.
I won't say a word, I swear.

22:04.932 --> 22:07.761
-Just, please don't hurt me.
-Who the hell is he?

22:07.891 --> 22:10.024
[Katie]
What are you going to do to him?

22:10.154 --> 22:12.722
Only one thing to do.
You're for the chop, George.

22:12.853 --> 22:14.463
-[Katie] No.
-Can't be helped.

22:14.594 --> 22:16.030
We can't let him go.

22:16.160 --> 22:18.206
No! Peggy, tell her no!

22:18.337 --> 22:19.903
I would, but she's not wrong.

22:20.034 --> 22:21.818
We let him go,
he'll be off to the law

22:21.949 --> 22:23.864
and then she's back in
the Tower for hanging again.

22:23.994 --> 22:25.866
Hanging? Again?
What do you mean?

22:25.996 --> 22:27.171
Thank you very much.
Very discreet.

22:27.302 --> 22:28.738
Sorry. Just slipped out.

22:28.869 --> 22:30.827
What are you talking about?

22:30.958 --> 22:32.655
I'll explain later, shall I?
When things are less hectic.

22:32.786 --> 22:33.917
Explain now!

22:37.747 --> 22:39.706
I told you.
I told you, tell her nowt.

22:39.836 --> 22:41.708
I said I was sorry.

22:41.838 --> 22:42.970
Any road, she's got a right
to know your history.

22:43.100 --> 22:46.103
-What history?
-Nothing.

22:46.234 --> 22:48.018
-Nothing really bad.
-[laughs]

22:48.149 --> 22:50.151
Shut it, you.

22:50.281 --> 22:51.805
[Katie] It must be worse
than what I've seen,

22:51.935 --> 22:54.416
or why would you be
ashamed to tell me?

22:54.547 --> 22:56.113
Fuck off!

22:58.072 --> 22:59.943
Fuck off, the pair of you!

23:00.074 --> 23:01.641
[groans]

23:17.439 --> 23:19.659
[Peggy]
We had a little sister.

23:19.789 --> 23:23.227
Mary Ann.
Three years younger than Bet.

23:23.358 --> 23:26.013
We called her May.

23:26.143 --> 23:30.974
When Bet was 11, they were
on their way to school,

23:31.105 --> 23:34.108
and May fell in the canal
and drowned.

23:34.238 --> 23:36.980
People said Bet pushed her in.

23:37.111 --> 23:38.634
But that's people.

23:38.765 --> 23:40.810
They'll think the worst of you.

23:40.941 --> 23:42.986
Did she?

23:43.117 --> 23:44.292
-Push her in?
-No, it was an accident.

23:44.423 --> 23:46.120
-I know it was.
-[George groaning]

23:46.250 --> 23:48.818
Bet would have died for her.
Hush.

23:51.908 --> 23:56.783
Well, ever since then,
she tries to be good.

23:56.913 --> 23:59.089
But bad luck just comes
after her, like George here.

23:59.220 --> 24:01.352
He raped her.

24:01.483 --> 24:03.877
And she does
as she's done by, our Bet.

24:05.444 --> 24:06.836
She's done some very bad things.

24:10.840 --> 24:13.277
Tell me.

24:13.408 --> 24:15.628
I'm not afraid.

24:15.758 --> 24:16.846
You should be.

24:25.986 --> 24:28.815
I've been looking for you.

24:28.945 --> 24:30.773
Well, you found me.

24:33.080 --> 24:34.951
Peggy's told me everything.

24:35.082 --> 24:39.216
About May and-- and what's
been done to you.

24:39.347 --> 24:41.741
What you've done.
Why didn't you tell me?

24:44.961 --> 24:47.094
I was trying to make
a good impression, all right?

24:49.444 --> 24:51.315
Sorry I wasn't honest.

24:51.446 --> 24:54.275
Now you know.

24:54.405 --> 24:56.233
Now you can fuck off.

24:58.671 --> 25:00.107
[exhales]

25:03.806 --> 25:05.068
I'd rather stay.

25:10.465 --> 25:13.990
- Really? You would?
-I would, but--

25:14.121 --> 25:17.080
Oh, here we go. But what?

25:17.211 --> 25:19.866
You can't just go around hurting
people when you feel like it.

25:19.996 --> 25:21.650
You've got to stop doing that.

25:23.826 --> 25:25.741
Well, I can try.

25:25.872 --> 25:27.482
-I'll do me best.
-No.

25:27.613 --> 25:30.006
You've got to promise
that you'll stop.

25:35.969 --> 25:38.014
All right.

25:38.145 --> 25:39.755
I promise.

25:39.886 --> 25:42.018
After George, that's me done.

25:42.149 --> 25:43.672
Not even George.

25:44.847 --> 25:46.109
Not even George?

25:46.240 --> 25:48.111
How's that gonna work?

25:48.242 --> 25:51.114
I don't know,
but we'll think of something.

25:51.245 --> 25:52.681
All right?

26:01.037 --> 26:04.693
[Daveboy] Here we go. Unto the
fucking breach, my dear friends.

26:04.824 --> 26:06.913
Eh?

26:07.043 --> 26:09.002
I said, "Here we go."

26:09.132 --> 26:12.005
Yeah. Here we go.

26:12.135 --> 26:15.095
[doorbell rings]

26:16.879 --> 26:18.098
You all right?

26:18.228 --> 26:20.927
You're as nervy as a blind cat.

26:21.057 --> 26:24.626
I'm good. This is the hand
we've been dealt.

26:24.757 --> 26:27.020
This is what we have to do.
That's what Bazza would say.

26:27.150 --> 26:29.196
Hmm.

26:31.285 --> 26:32.373
Morning.

26:32.503 --> 26:34.201
Come in.

26:40.511 --> 26:43.819
They're all through there.
Cup of tea?

26:43.950 --> 26:45.299
Two sugars, please, love.

26:45.429 --> 26:46.866
[indistinct chatter]

26:48.432 --> 26:49.433
I'm surprised to see you here.

26:49.564 --> 26:51.261
It's just business.

26:51.392 --> 26:53.089
I thought you had
more self-respect.

26:53.220 --> 26:54.874
Won't happen again.

26:55.004 --> 26:57.180
Oh, that.

26:57.311 --> 26:59.052
No, that was nothing.

26:59.182 --> 27:01.750
I meant this idiotic crime spree
you're going on.

27:01.881 --> 27:04.187
Oh, that. Piece of cake.

27:04.318 --> 27:06.886
Hmm. How do you take your tea?

27:07.016 --> 27:09.018
Last of the pot,
dab of milk, no sugar.

27:14.241 --> 27:17.548
The night's takings are kept
in the manager's office

27:17.679 --> 27:20.029
in the basement,
which we access via this door.

27:20.160 --> 27:22.902
Here.

27:23.032 --> 27:24.686
Now, the main event
is scheduled for

27:24.817 --> 27:26.253
-five four-minute rounds...
-[Daveboy] Ah, thank you.

27:26.383 --> 27:27.907
...with a minute's break
between each round.

27:28.037 --> 27:30.344
We're gonna use
that 25-minute window

27:30.474 --> 27:32.868
to get in and out

27:32.999 --> 27:36.306
while every eye is on the ring.

27:38.657 --> 27:41.050
'Cause when the fight is over,

27:41.181 --> 27:45.185
every one of these exit routes
will be jammed with people.

27:46.273 --> 27:47.317
Questions?

27:48.492 --> 27:49.929
-Aye.
-Yeah?

27:51.147 --> 27:54.368
What if the fight ends early?

27:54.498 --> 27:56.587
The main event always goes
to the final round.

27:56.718 --> 27:59.112
They want to sell
all the beer and the pies.

27:59.242 --> 28:00.809
Can't have punters
leaving early.

28:02.202 --> 28:04.117
[Daveboy] Aye, but what
if there's a-- a knockout

28:04.247 --> 28:06.510
or a fucking submission
or something?

28:06.641 --> 28:09.557
[Alfred] The fights
are staged, Daveboy.

28:09.688 --> 28:13.300
What, you mean, like, fixed?

28:13.430 --> 28:15.737
-No. No, they're not.
-[laughter]

28:15.868 --> 28:19.436
- [Banjo] Are you soft?
- Everyone knows they're fixed.

28:19.567 --> 28:23.136
Well, s-some of them are bent,
maybe, I get that, yeah.

28:23.266 --> 28:24.964
It's human nature
to cheat, but...

28:26.269 --> 28:27.662
A-All of them?

28:27.793 --> 28:30.491
-Yes, mate.
-Oh, for fuck's sake.

28:30.621 --> 28:32.493
And here's more bad news
for you.

28:32.623 --> 28:34.713
Father Christmas
is bollocks, too.

28:34.843 --> 28:37.672
-Shut the fuck up, Banjo.
-Steady on, lads.

28:37.803 --> 28:39.718
-Shut yourself.
-What did I just say?

28:39.848 --> 28:42.111
Who the fuck are you
to say shite to me?

28:42.242 --> 28:44.331
-I'm warning you.
-Silence!

28:47.987 --> 28:50.206
Jesus.

28:50.337 --> 28:52.121
Can you look at me, Melanie?

28:53.688 --> 28:57.213
I have commanded
a thousand men in battle.

28:57.344 --> 28:59.868
I have taken cities
and sat with kings.

28:59.999 --> 29:02.479
Sat with fucking kings.

29:02.610 --> 29:08.268
And yet here I am, with a rabble
of squabbling thieves.

29:09.399 --> 29:11.401
Pitiful, isn't it?

29:13.447 --> 29:16.015
You gonna say something,
darling?

29:16.145 --> 29:18.017
[Melanie]
God, I'm bored.

29:18.147 --> 29:21.890
No, no, no. Don't-don't...
don't leave just yet.

29:22.021 --> 29:23.979
Melanie...

29:24.110 --> 29:26.895
You have to be polite
to our guests.

29:28.505 --> 29:30.246
Low creatures they may be,

29:30.377 --> 29:34.207
but they do pay
for all of your fucking shoes.

29:35.295 --> 29:38.211
Hmm.

29:38.341 --> 29:41.649
Thank you all very much
for my fucking shoes.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.738
And thank you for putting up

29:43.869 --> 29:47.046
with my husband's
appalling manners.

29:48.177 --> 29:49.788
[chuckles]

29:53.879 --> 29:56.272
Ah, God, I love that woman.
[chuckles]

29:56.403 --> 29:58.840
Brave as a lion.

30:02.365 --> 30:04.106
Now, where was I?

30:04.237 --> 30:07.806
We have 25 minutes,
no more, no less.

30:14.464 --> 30:16.553
-Clear.
-Go. Go.

30:22.081 --> 30:23.473
♪

30:38.445 --> 30:40.229
[whistling, loud chatter]

30:43.624 --> 30:46.148
[cheering]

30:50.022 --> 30:54.156
Ladies and gentlemen,
it's time for the main event.

30:54.287 --> 30:57.725
A five-round contest

30:57.856 --> 31:01.772
for the Ladies Catchweight
Championship of England.

31:01.903 --> 31:06.603
And coming to the ring first,
the fighting pride of Poplar,

31:06.734 --> 31:10.085
the masked mistress of mayhem,

31:10.216 --> 31:12.566
the meanest woman
in the home counties--

31:12.696 --> 31:16.352
Mad Janet Murphy.

31:16.483 --> 31:18.615
♪

31:18.746 --> 31:21.096
-[crowd booing]
-[Murphy] You wankers.

31:21.227 --> 31:22.576
You paid to see me.

31:22.706 --> 31:24.186
You paid.

31:24.317 --> 31:26.449
I can't hear you.

31:26.580 --> 31:28.756
Oh, now I can hear you.

31:28.887 --> 31:31.367
Come on. I can't hear you.

31:43.814 --> 31:46.252
[Troy]
Wait. You two, wait here.

31:46.382 --> 31:49.211
Anyone comes through
those doors, deal with them.

31:49.342 --> 31:51.083
-[Banjo] Yes, sir.
-[Ring announcer] And now,

31:51.213 --> 31:52.736
your golden girl.

31:52.867 --> 31:57.741
the Venus of violence,
the Aphrodite of affray.

31:57.872 --> 32:01.528
The undisputed
catchweight champion of England,

32:01.658 --> 32:03.747
Rowdy Rose Perkins.

32:03.878 --> 32:06.272
[cheering, applause]

32:06.402 --> 32:08.317
♪

32:12.452 --> 32:14.062
Yeah!

32:16.238 --> 32:18.066
Come on!
[whoops]

32:26.640 --> 32:28.337
[Alfred]
No trouble.

32:28.468 --> 32:31.340
Let's all go home
happy tonight, yeah?

32:31.471 --> 32:33.081
[bell rings]

32:39.435 --> 32:41.220
For fuck's sake.

32:41.350 --> 32:43.570
Sorry about this. Won't be long.

32:43.700 --> 32:44.832
I don't know the combination,
so there's no use asking.

32:44.963 --> 32:46.616
[Troy]
We know. Thank you.

32:46.747 --> 32:48.401
Do you know what happened
to the last blokes

32:48.531 --> 32:50.185
that tried this?

32:50.316 --> 32:51.447
[Alfred]
The Barratt Brothers?

32:51.578 --> 32:53.493
[Troy]
Ha! Amateurs.

32:53.623 --> 32:54.537
You're laughing now.

32:54.668 --> 32:55.625
Wait till your bollocks

32:55.756 --> 32:57.236
are nailed to the floor.

32:57.366 --> 32:58.367
[Alfred]
Everybody always talks about

32:58.498 --> 32:59.803
nailing bollocks to the floor,

32:59.934 --> 33:01.544
but nobody actually
does it, do they?

33:01.675 --> 33:03.633
-You'll see.
-[Daveboy] Empty words, pal.

33:06.549 --> 33:09.117
[shushes]
Down.

33:17.386 --> 33:19.475
[Alfred]
Slow down. We got time.

33:20.607 --> 33:21.738
21 minutes.

33:33.315 --> 33:35.665
[crowd cheering]

33:40.322 --> 33:42.411
[Troy]
Shit.

33:53.335 --> 33:54.858
[drill stops]

33:54.989 --> 33:56.686
[Ring announcer]
Seconds away from round two.

33:59.515 --> 34:01.430
-[Alfred] 14 minutes.
-[Troy] Nearly there.

34:02.736 --> 34:04.607
[Troy]
Ah, this is the life, eh?

34:04.738 --> 34:07.741
[chuckles]
Gets the blood flowing.

34:10.700 --> 34:12.354
Fuck me, it's hot.

34:12.485 --> 34:13.573
[thudding]

34:20.797 --> 34:22.234
What the hell's wrong with you?

34:22.364 --> 34:23.931
What's wrong with you?

34:24.062 --> 34:25.802
[Perkins]
What the fuck?

34:25.933 --> 34:28.414
[Murphy]
Just get back to the routine.

34:28.544 --> 34:30.416
-What?
-[Referee] Three...

34:30.546 --> 34:32.461
[Murphy]
Wait, wait.

34:32.592 --> 34:33.680
[yelling]

34:42.645 --> 34:43.733
Ease up.

34:48.782 --> 34:51.872
No, you fucking ease up.

34:52.002 --> 34:54.744
You bitch!

34:54.875 --> 34:57.617
Easy, girls. Easy.

35:03.840 --> 35:05.625
12 minutes.

35:05.755 --> 35:07.583
[Referee]
Break it up, ladies!

35:07.714 --> 35:09.498
[crowd exclaiming]

35:09.629 --> 35:11.631
Stop that!

35:13.415 --> 35:14.982
[Troy]
All right. Desk, please.

35:15.113 --> 35:16.505
-[Alfred] Daveboy?
-[Daveboy] Yeah?

35:16.636 --> 35:18.507
[Alfred]
You three, heads down.

35:28.604 --> 35:30.606
[bell ringing]

35:30.737 --> 35:33.435
[indistinct shouting]

35:38.832 --> 35:40.747
♪

35:41.965 --> 35:45.447
[shouting continues]

35:45.578 --> 35:47.623
[crowd gasping]

35:47.754 --> 35:49.712
[bell ringing]

35:56.589 --> 35:58.156
-[microphone feedback]
-[clears throat]

36:02.160 --> 36:03.552
[Troy]
Fire in the hole.

36:05.511 --> 36:07.600
Uh, ladies and gentlemen,

36:07.730 --> 36:09.863
uh, we regret
to inform you that,

36:09.993 --> 36:12.996
for unavoidable medical reasons,

36:13.127 --> 36:16.652
this concludes
this evening's entertainment.

36:16.783 --> 36:19.351
Thank you very much. Please
leave in an orderly fashion.

36:19.481 --> 36:21.048
[crowd booing]

36:21.179 --> 36:23.442
Thank you and good night.

36:23.572 --> 36:25.574
[Alfred]
They're ten minutes early.

36:25.705 --> 36:28.447
[Daveboy] I told you the fights
weren't fixed. Let's go.

36:28.577 --> 36:29.970
We haven't finished the job.

36:30.100 --> 36:30.840
[Alfred] Well, we can't
blow the safe.

36:30.971 --> 36:32.886
Everyone will hear it.

36:33.016 --> 36:34.453
The exit routes will
be jammed with people.

36:34.583 --> 36:37.586
[Troy]
Who dares wins, eh?

36:40.981 --> 36:42.417
[people screaming]

36:42.548 --> 36:45.768
[Man] It's a bomb! It's a bomb!

36:45.899 --> 36:48.206
-[moaning, coughing]
-[high-pitched ringing]

36:50.033 --> 36:51.774
[Daveboy]
For fuck's sake!

36:51.905 --> 36:53.689
What the fuck was that?

36:53.820 --> 36:56.475
Oh, Jesus.

36:56.605 --> 36:57.911
We need to get out of here now.

36:58.041 --> 36:59.956
We have to leave!

37:12.578 --> 37:14.406
[Alfred]
Bags, now.

37:17.757 --> 37:20.716
♪

37:20.847 --> 37:23.502
[distant clamoring]

37:23.632 --> 37:26.505
♪ I want you to know
that I love you, baby♪

37:26.635 --> 37:29.812
♪ Want you to know that I care♪

37:29.943 --> 37:31.814
♪ I'm so happy
when you're around me♪

37:31.945 --> 37:34.556
♪ But I'm sad when you're
not there♪

37:34.687 --> 37:38.125
♪ So tell me,
whatcha gonna do about it?♪

37:38.256 --> 37:40.954
-♪ Oh, yeah♪
-♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪

37:41.084 --> 37:44.174
-♪ I go crazy♪
-♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪

37:44.305 --> 37:47.700
-♪ You're so nice♪
-♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪

37:47.830 --> 37:50.050
♪ I want you to give me
your sweet, sweet kisses...♪

37:50.180 --> 37:52.574
-[people screaming]
-[Banjo] Get back!

37:52.705 --> 37:54.663
Fucking get back!

37:57.187 --> 38:00.190
[clamoring]

38:00.321 --> 38:03.063
♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪

