38:07.154 --> 38:08.677
-♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪
-♪ Oh, yeah♪

38:08.808 --> 38:11.898
♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪

38:12.028 --> 38:13.726
♪ Now you hear the music...♪

38:15.684 --> 38:17.817
What?

38:35.400 --> 38:38.925
♪ I want you to know
that I love you, baby♪

38:39.055 --> 38:41.231
♪ I said this before,
but I care♪

38:41.362 --> 38:43.146
♪ You know that I'm so happy♪

38:43.277 --> 38:45.497
♪ When you're around me
and I'm sad...♪

38:45.627 --> 38:47.499
Get out of my way!

38:47.629 --> 38:49.675
♪ Whatcha gonna do about it?♪

38:49.805 --> 38:50.850
Get out of my way!

38:50.980 --> 38:52.982
Die, you evil bastard!

38:53.113 --> 38:54.767
-[yelling]
-No, don't!

38:54.897 --> 38:56.856
Stop!

39:01.077 --> 39:02.775
[Daveboy, distorted]
Alfie?

39:02.905 --> 39:03.993
Alfie, move!

39:12.088 --> 39:14.003
[panting]

39:17.964 --> 39:19.835
[distant screaming]

39:32.631 --> 39:34.502
[laughter]

39:42.728 --> 39:45.774
[distant chatter]

39:45.905 --> 39:47.994
[Banjo]
Come on. Where's my...

39:48.124 --> 39:50.039
It's beautiful.

39:50.170 --> 39:53.129
Yes, we did it, boys.
We fucking done it.

39:53.260 --> 39:55.001
Oh, yeah.
You fucking done it all right.

39:55.131 --> 39:56.568
-Done it good and proper.
-What's your problem?

39:56.698 --> 39:58.178
There's dead civvies
back there

39:58.308 --> 39:59.614
and you're all laughing
like we done a good job.

39:59.745 --> 40:02.182
Get to fuck. Accidents happen.

40:02.312 --> 40:05.011
As if you never killed
a civvy before.

40:05.141 --> 40:07.187
I have. But never in a panic,

40:07.317 --> 40:08.928
with my mask off,
in front of a hundred witnesses.

40:09.058 --> 40:10.799
-I've never done that.
-Fuck off.

40:10.930 --> 40:12.801
-I didn't panic.
-Eh, you kind of did.

40:12.932 --> 40:14.847
-Fuck you, too!
-Shut it!

40:16.283 --> 40:17.545
All of you.

40:20.287 --> 40:23.856
Bad things happen in combat.
We move on.

40:23.986 --> 40:25.901
Combat, my arse.

40:26.032 --> 40:29.035
We're not soldiers.

40:29.165 --> 40:31.037
We're thieves. Murderers now.

40:31.167 --> 40:33.692
Oh, do stop whimpering, boy.

40:33.822 --> 40:36.912
-I've had enough of it.
-Alfie.

40:37.043 --> 40:38.958
Let's go home.

40:43.049 --> 40:45.094
We'll have a brew, eh?

40:47.401 --> 40:48.968
Bye-bye, Alfie.

40:54.364 --> 40:56.454
[laughs]

40:57.759 --> 41:00.936
[pours drink]

41:01.067 --> 41:02.938
No worries, Alfie.

41:03.069 --> 41:05.288
We'll be in America
before the plods catch Banjo.

41:05.419 --> 41:07.943
-No worries.
-Don't be so hard on yourself.

41:08.074 --> 41:11.599
Now, we may be murderers,
but we are rich murderers.

41:30.052 --> 41:32.011
[door opens]

41:34.796 --> 41:36.624
[door closes]

41:39.453 --> 41:40.976
-Mum.
-Alfie.

41:41.107 --> 41:43.022
[exhales]

41:43.152 --> 41:46.242
I haven't seen you for days.
I was worried about you.

41:46.373 --> 41:49.289
Uh, wheeling and dealing,
you know.

41:49.419 --> 41:50.638
I've sorted the money.

41:52.901 --> 41:55.382
We can be off
to America after all.

41:55.513 --> 41:57.036
Where did you get the money?

41:57.166 --> 41:58.994
Eh, don't worry about that.

41:59.125 --> 42:01.040
Well, how?

42:02.345 --> 42:06.175
Well, it's just business,
you know.

42:07.568 --> 42:09.527
It wasn't
at the wrestling, was it?

42:10.440 --> 42:12.138
What?

42:12.268 --> 42:13.966
No.

42:15.489 --> 42:17.709
There's people dead.

42:22.061 --> 42:23.192
Yeah.

42:23.323 --> 42:25.151
I heard about that.

42:25.281 --> 42:27.327
Shocking.

42:27.457 --> 42:31.984
No, no, me, no, um,
I just closed a nice deal.

42:32.114 --> 42:34.595
Smuggling petrol,
if you must know.

42:35.988 --> 42:37.206
Look at me.

42:39.382 --> 42:41.080
Tell me it wasn't you
robbed the wrestling

42:41.210 --> 42:43.125
and killed those people.

42:44.257 --> 42:46.041
It wasn't me.

42:49.001 --> 42:50.959
Oh, my God.

42:56.095 --> 42:58.750
Oh, Alfie.

42:58.880 --> 43:01.013
Look, things went wrong.

43:01.143 --> 43:03.102
-It was never my-- Oh!
-Get out.

43:03.232 --> 43:04.233
-Mum...
-Get out!

43:04.364 --> 43:05.452
I don't want to hear it.

43:05.583 --> 43:07.149
I don't want to look at you.

43:07.280 --> 43:09.282
Thank God your dad
isn't alive today.

43:09.412 --> 43:11.023
-Now get out!
-Look, Mum,

43:11.153 --> 43:12.328
it's a terrible,
tragic thing what happened.

43:12.459 --> 43:15.244
Look, I'm ashamed
and I am sorry.

43:15.375 --> 43:17.290
But w-we... we have to try
and move forward, you know?

43:17.420 --> 43:19.640
This tragedy is all
the more reason we have to get

43:19.771 --> 43:21.381
-to America, quick as you can.
-For the millionth time,

43:21.511 --> 43:24.123
I am not going to America.

43:24.253 --> 43:26.212
Least of all
with a murderous robber.

43:26.342 --> 43:28.867
-Look, Mum, please.
-Enough!

43:39.529 --> 43:41.749
♪

43:57.765 --> 44:00.289
You can send Daveboy
to fetch your clothes.

44:02.161 --> 44:04.032
Get out.

44:22.572 --> 44:24.662
[door slams]

44:32.931 --> 44:34.802
♪

44:40.939 --> 44:42.897
[door opens]

44:43.028 --> 44:44.812
[footsteps approaching]

44:47.162 --> 44:49.208
Hello, Jimmy.

44:49.338 --> 44:50.992
Aren't we having
a council meeting?

44:51.123 --> 44:52.777
Postponed.

44:52.907 --> 44:54.996
Oh. Well, good.

44:55.127 --> 44:58.434
I, uh, I wanted
to talk to you in private

44:58.565 --> 45:00.959
about this Stormcloud disgrace.

45:01.089 --> 45:03.004
Disgrace?

45:03.135 --> 45:06.007
That's rich coming from you,
my friend.

45:06.138 --> 45:08.923
I'm not sure I like that tone
in your voice.

45:09.054 --> 45:11.621
Oh, really? Well, that won't do.

45:11.752 --> 45:14.276
I shall be more cheerful,
shall I?

45:14.407 --> 45:16.757
-Must keep the old girl happy.
-Jimmy.

45:16.888 --> 45:20.108
Perhaps a little, a little dance
would please you, hmm?

45:20.239 --> 45:22.589
-Hmm?
-For God's sake, Jimmy.

45:22.720 --> 45:25.244
-What's wrong?
-I mean, pretty bloody spry

45:25.374 --> 45:27.115
for a mad old cripple.

45:27.246 --> 45:28.987
Your new friend dance as well
as I do?

45:30.553 --> 45:33.121
Oh, of course.
Sorry, I'm being a bit slow.

45:33.252 --> 45:34.862
Iron deficiency, I suspect.

45:34.993 --> 45:38.039
This is about Aziz.

45:38.170 --> 45:39.388
No, I was going to give you
a briefing on that.

45:39.519 --> 45:41.303
A briefing? Good.

45:41.434 --> 45:45.003
Well, then, everything's
tickety-boo, isn't it?

45:45.133 --> 45:47.962
I went to speak to him
on your behalf.

45:48.093 --> 45:50.051
I thought you'd approve.

45:50.182 --> 45:52.401
Secret meetings
with the prime minister

45:52.532 --> 45:55.274
of the English League.

45:55.404 --> 45:57.406
Whispering in dark corners.

45:57.537 --> 46:00.061
And I have to hear this
from underlings.

46:00.192 --> 46:02.803
Well, wouldn't you like
to hear what he had to say?

46:02.934 --> 46:05.501
No! I damn well do not
want to hear what he had to say!

46:05.632 --> 46:08.374
How can I trust what I hear?

46:08.504 --> 46:10.289
How do I know you're not
working for him now?

46:10.419 --> 46:13.248
This is absurd.

46:13.379 --> 46:15.642
Do you see what you've done?

46:15.773 --> 46:19.080
If I don't know that I can trust
you, then you're no good to me.

46:19.211 --> 46:22.301
And I can't know,
not for certain, not now.

46:22.431 --> 46:24.085
Jimmy, you are not yourself.

46:24.216 --> 46:26.305
Have you been taking
your medication properly?

46:26.435 --> 46:29.743
Of course you'd go to that.
I'm-I'm crazy? I'm-I'm paranoid?

46:29.874 --> 46:32.180
How-how long have
we known each other?

46:33.312 --> 46:34.226
All my life.

46:34.356 --> 46:36.358
Exactly.

46:39.274 --> 46:41.276
Is there no one I can trust?

46:42.712 --> 46:45.063
-Am I completely bloody alone?
-Jimmy.

46:47.456 --> 46:49.676
You broke my heart, Frances.

46:49.807 --> 46:51.939
You broke my fucking heart.

46:53.071 --> 46:54.115
Guards.

46:56.291 --> 46:58.380
No, don't do this, Jimmy. Jimmy.

46:58.511 --> 47:00.818
Jimmy, this is insane.

47:02.515 --> 47:04.082
I was trying to help you!

47:04.212 --> 47:05.823
Yes, of course, Frances.
You're right.

47:05.953 --> 47:07.955
I'm crazy. You were
just trying to help me.

47:10.088 --> 47:11.393
Thank you, Frances.

47:17.747 --> 47:19.837
[explosions]

47:28.323 --> 47:30.238
[muffled shouting]

47:55.263 --> 47:57.135
♪

48:06.796 --> 48:08.886
[distant explosion]

48:11.105 --> 48:13.020
[machine whirring]

48:43.094 --> 48:45.313
♪

48:55.584 --> 48:58.457
[air-raid siren wailing]

49:06.421 --> 49:08.249
[indistinct chatter]

49:19.782 --> 49:21.959
♪

49:50.378 --> 49:52.380
♪

50:02.651 --> 50:04.523
[indistinct chatter]

50:29.722 --> 50:32.290
Good evening, Mrs. Troy.

50:33.769 --> 50:35.510
My name is Melanie.

50:36.642 --> 50:39.427
You look tired.

50:39.558 --> 50:41.603
You look pretty good, Melanie.

50:41.734 --> 50:44.519
Considering. Walk into a door?

50:44.650 --> 50:46.304
[laughs softly]

50:48.306 --> 50:50.264
No.

50:50.395 --> 50:53.224
-I'm sorry.
-Don't be.

50:53.354 --> 50:55.878
I detest pity.

50:56.009 --> 50:58.185
Why are you here?

51:03.669 --> 51:05.758
Why do you think?

51:09.718 --> 51:12.199
He hurt you,
so you want to hurt him.

51:14.071 --> 51:17.335
Nobody can hurt Gully.
He's made of bones.

51:18.423 --> 51:19.728
Mm.

51:23.080 --> 51:25.604
Would you like me to leave?

51:27.475 --> 51:29.129
No.

51:37.659 --> 51:40.401
Tape's rolling.
Whenever you're ready.

51:44.492 --> 51:46.407
♪

51:48.931 --> 51:53.327
♪ For you, I was a flame♪

51:53.458 --> 51:58.898
♪ Love is a losing game♪

51:59.028 --> 52:04.338
♪ Five-story fire as you came♪

52:04.469 --> 52:09.517
♪ Love is a losing game♪

52:09.648 --> 52:14.740
♪ One I wish I never played♪

52:14.870 --> 52:20.746
♪ Oh, what a mess we made♪

52:20.876 --> 52:25.359
♪ And now the final frame♪

52:25.490 --> 52:30.147
♪ Love is a losing game♪

52:33.672 --> 52:37.893
♪ Played out by the band♪

52:38.024 --> 52:44.378
♪ Love is a losing hand♪

52:44.509 --> 52:49.383
♪ More than I could stand♪

52:49.514 --> 52:54.736
♪ Love is a losing hand♪

52:54.867 --> 52:59.785
♪ Self-professed, profound♪

52:59.915 --> 53:05.704
♪ Till the chips were down♪

53:05.834 --> 53:10.535
♪ Though you're a gambling man♪

53:10.665 --> 53:15.801
♪ Love is a losing hand♪

53:19.544 --> 53:23.939
♪ Though I battle blind♪

53:24.070 --> 53:29.597
♪ Love is a fate resigned♪

53:29.728 --> 53:34.646
♪ Memories mar my mind♪

53:34.776 --> 53:40.434
♪ Love, it is a fate resigned♪

53:40.565 --> 53:45.831
♪ Over futile odds♪

53:45.961 --> 53:51.402
♪ And laughed at by the gods♪

53:51.532 --> 53:56.015
♪ And now the final frame♪

53:56.145 --> 54:01.499
♪ Love is a losing game.♪

54:05.329 --> 54:07.418
[Troy]
You remember that night raid

54:07.548 --> 54:09.463
in the Sulawesi channel?

54:09.594 --> 54:11.639
[Banjo]
Aye. I remember.

54:11.770 --> 54:14.076
A full moon.

54:14.207 --> 54:16.557
Clear as day.

54:16.688 --> 54:18.690
You went in first.

54:18.820 --> 54:20.735
Buggers all dug in
at the tree line.

54:20.866 --> 54:21.780
Yeah.

54:23.260 --> 54:26.828
Got us out of a tight spot.

54:26.959 --> 54:30.267
You're a damn
good soldier, Banjo.

54:33.357 --> 54:35.663
There were little turtles
on the beach.

54:37.709 --> 54:39.580
Hundreds of them.

54:39.711 --> 54:41.756
Turtles, you say?

54:41.887 --> 54:44.063
Really?

54:44.193 --> 54:46.631
I don't remember that.

54:46.761 --> 54:50.112
It was that quiet at first,

54:50.243 --> 54:52.550
before the gunfire.

54:55.117 --> 54:58.425
You could hear them all
making for the water.

55:01.080 --> 55:04.605
Thousands of little flippers
in the sand.

55:06.955 --> 55:08.827
[wings fluttering]

55:12.091 --> 55:14.049
♪

55:21.143 --> 55:23.320
♪

55:52.261 --> 55:54.351
♪

